      "span_text": "Using antibodies against myosin heavy chain IIB (MHC-IIB), IIA (MHC-IIB), and 1 (MHC-I), no significant difference was found in fiber-type composition between CTRL and MICU1-smKO TA muscles: type IIB fibers were predominant (55%-65%), type IIA fibers were mildly frequent (5%-6%), and almost no (< 1%) MHC-I-positive fibers were detected, as previously reported for TA muscle in mice"
